nce. From mystical outpourings in ancient Palestine to the Kabbalah Centre, and from attitudes towards gender to mystical contributions to Jewish messianic movements, this volume explores the various expressions of Jewish mysticism from antiquity to the present day in an engaging style appropriate for students and non-specialists alike.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aCabalaxHistory. 0aJudaismxHistory. 0aMysticismxJudaismxHistory. 7aRELIGION / Judaism / Rituals & Practice.2bisacsh1 aCoudert, Allison P., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFine, Lawrence, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGiller, Pinchas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGoldish, Matt, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGreenspahn, Frederick E., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aLachter, Hartley, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMagid, Shaul, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMyers, Jody, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSwartz, Michael D., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTirosh-Samuelson, Hava, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWolfson, Elliot R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertNew York University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z97831107064440 cprintz978081473286140uhttps://doi.org/10.18574/nyu/9780814732885.001.000140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780814732885423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780814732885/original  a978-3-11-070644-4  New York University Press Backlist eBook-Package 200